<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="363" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,867,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1443,1470]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Comments.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2995036303" country="China" location="This" municipality="Northern" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:555ACB66A13BFF87FF48FD17FAFFCBEC:D82C2CABA13BFF84FE88FA22FE5AC9C3" box="[343,393,1444,1470]" country="China" municipality="Northern" name="This" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">This</location>
new genus is known only from two male specimens from mid-elevations in 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1254,1355,1444,1470]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Northern</collectingMunicipality>
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1432,1444,1470]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">China</collectingCountry>
, one was collected by the author and represents the 
<typeStatus box="[745,843,1480,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen. The second individual that was in much better condition is known only from a series of high quality photographs taken in the field (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1274,1516,1542]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1444,1469]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1002,1027]" captionStartId-2="3.[151,250,1979,2004]" captionTargetBox-0="[156,1432,489,1418]" captionTargetBox-1="[250,1336,181,977]" captionTargetBox-2="[295,1291,1085,1953]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[156,1432,489,1418]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[250,1336,181,977]" captionTargetId-2="figure@3.[295,1291,1085,1953]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Sinothereva shangui gen. et sp. n., male, photographed in the field, Xinglong, China (Photograph copyright: Shan Gui). (Link: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/54918804)" captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Sinothereva shangui gen. et sp. n., male, photographed in the field, Xinglong, China (Photograph copyright: Shan Gui). (Link: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/54918833)" captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Sinothereva shangui gen. et sp. n., male, photographed in the field, Xinglong, China (Photograph copyright: Shan Gui). (Link: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/54919032)" figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954481" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954483" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954485" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3954481/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3954483/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3954485/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
) by the nature photographer, Shan Gui. The specimen was not collected. These images were posted to iNaturalist for subsequent community-based identification. It was here through serendipity, that the author first discovered this distinctive new stiletto fly; it was subsequently compared with the previously collected specimen (but in poor condition) from the same region and confirmed as the same species
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,867,2011]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,153,468]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="363" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
This new genus and species is a member of 
<taxonomicName box="[686,812,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Therevinae">Therevinae</taxonomicName>
although it is not clear to which genus group it belongs. The most important and immediately diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authority="Winterton, 2020" authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[817,950,1732,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[817,950,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[956,1031,1733,1759]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are the lack of scutellar macrosetae, the male frons much wider than the ocellar tubercle, and absence of both parafacial setae and the hind coxal knob. Also distinctive is the extensive setal pile on the entire body, including the head and femora. Some of these characteristics can also be found in 
<emphasis box="[511,669,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[511,665,1840,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aristothereva</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but 
<taxonomicName authority="Winterton, 2020" authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[722,855,1840,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[722,855,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[863,940,1841,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be differentiated by the very small and narrow arista (large and conical in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[549,700,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,700,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lack of scutellar macrosetae (numerous in some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[1276,1427,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1276,1427,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in the male genitalia by the reduced posteriorly directed processes on the gonocoxites (well-developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Indeed, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[371,504,1948,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[371,504,1948,1974]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows considerable affinity for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[868,1019,1948,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,1019,1948,1974]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and these two Palaearctic genera are likely closely related. Broader relationships of 
<taxonomicName authority="Winterton, 2020" authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[691,824,1984,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[691,824,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[833,911,1985,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[980,1131,1984,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[980,1131,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to other therevine genera are less clear. Morphological synapomorphies uniting members of either the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1796" box="[1015,1106,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Thereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1106,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Thereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Irwin &amp; Lyneborg" authorityYear="1981" box="[1144,1279,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Pandivirilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1144,1279,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Pandivirilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus groups are not well defined (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Holston, K. C. &amp; Irwin, M. E. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M." box="[442,671,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" pagination="279 - 296" refId="ref3144" refString="Holston, K. C., Irwin, M. E. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M. (2007) Monophyly and phylogenetic relationships of Thereva and therevine genus-groups (Insecta: Diptera: Therevidae) based on EF- 1 α, 28 S rDNA and mitochondrial 16 S rDNA sequences. Invertebrate Systematics, 21, 279 - 296." type="journal article" year="2007">
Holston 
<emphasis box="[539,590,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Winterton, S. L. &amp; Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gaimari, S. D. &amp; Hauser, M. &amp; Hill, H. N. &amp; Holston, K. C. &amp; Irwin, M. E. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. &amp; Metz, M. A. &amp; Turco, F. &amp; Webb, D. &amp; Yang, L. &amp; Yeates, D. K. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M." box="[684,939,189,216]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" pagination="144 - 161" refId="ref3440" refString="Winterton, S. L., Hardy, N. B., Gaimari, S. D., Hauser, M., Hill, H. N., Holston, K. C., Irwin, M. E., Lambkin, C. L., Metz, M. A., Turco, F., Webb, D., Yang, L., Yeates, D. K. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M. (2016) The phylogeny of stiletto flies (Diptera: Therevidae). Systematic Entomology, 41, 144 - 161." type="journal article" year="2016">
Winterton 
<emphasis box="[805,856,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Winterton, 2020" authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[1009,1142,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1009,1142,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1150,1227,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[1285,1436,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1285,1436,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibit characteristics of both. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyneborg" authorityName="Lyneborg" authorityYear="1978" box="[498,768,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Neotherevella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,654,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Neotherevella</emphasis>
Lyneborg
</taxonomicName>
appears to be related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[1043,1194,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1194,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Winterton, 2020" authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[1249,1382,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1249,1382,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="2" pageNumber="363" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and is found in the Palaearctic and Afrotropical regions. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyneborg" authorityYear="1978" box="[813,969,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Neotherevella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,969,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Neotherevella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a similar habitus with extensive erect whitish to silvery setal pile, male frons usually wider than the ocellar tubercle and parafacial setae absent, amongst other features. In contrast with 
<taxonomicName authority="Winterton, 2020" authorityName="Winterton" authorityYear="2020" box="[498,631,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Sinothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[498,631,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Sinothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[638,714,333,359]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyneborg" authorityYear="1978" box="[782,938,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Neotherevella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[782,938,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Neotherevella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[992,1143,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[992,1143,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have scutellar macrosetae present. 
<bibRefCitation author="Holston, K. C. &amp; Irwin, M. E. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M." box="[247,483,369,395]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" pagination="279 - 296" refId="ref3144" refString="Holston, K. C., Irwin, M. E. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M. (2007) Monophyly and phylogenetic relationships of Thereva and therevine genus-groups (Insecta: Diptera: Therevidae) based on EF- 1 α, 28 S rDNA and mitochondrial 16 S rDNA sequences. Invertebrate Systematics, 21, 279 - 296." type="journal article" year="2007">
Holston 
<emphasis box="[344,394,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1921" box="[620,771,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Aristothereva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[620,771,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Aristothereva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyneborg" authorityYear="1978" box="[828,984,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Neotherevella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,984,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Neotherevella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as part of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Irwin &amp; Lyneborg" authorityYear="1981" box="[1147,1282,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Pandivirilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1282,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Pandivirilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group, although these genera were not sampled in any of the published phylogenetic analyses to confirm this hypothesis (
<bibRefCitation author="Holston, K. C. &amp; Irwin, M. E. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M." box="[161,385,441,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" pagination="279 - 296" refId="ref3144" refString="Holston, K. C., Irwin, M. E. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M. (2007) Monophyly and phylogenetic relationships of Thereva and therevine genus-groups (Insecta: Diptera: Therevidae) based on EF- 1 α, 28 S rDNA and mitochondrial 16 S rDNA sequences. Invertebrate Systematics, 21, 279 - 296." type="journal article" year="2007">
Holston 
<emphasis box="[256,305,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Winterton, S. L. &amp; Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gaimari, S. D. &amp; Hauser, M. &amp; Hill, H. N. &amp; Holston, K. C. &amp; Irwin, M. E. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. &amp; Metz, M. A. &amp; Turco, F. &amp; Webb, D. &amp; Yang, L. &amp; Yeates, D. K. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M." box="[396,647,441,468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" pagination="144 - 161" refId="ref3440" refString="Winterton, S. L., Hardy, N. B., Gaimari, S. D., Hauser, M., Hill, H. N., Holston, K. C., Irwin, M. E., Lambkin, C. L., Metz, M. A., Turco, F., Webb, D., Yang, L., Yeates, D. K. &amp; Wiegmann, B. M. (2016) The phylogeny of stiletto flies (Diptera: Therevidae). Systematic Entomology, 41, 144 - 161." type="journal article" year="2016">
Winterton 
<emphasis box="[516,565,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954481" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3954481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" startId="2.[151,250,1444,1469]" targetBox="[156,1432,489,1418]" targetPageId="2">
